    "On the other hand, FCC(AK)[k, d] has enjoyed much attention and has been resolved affirmatively in some non-trivial cases.",
    "The case of FCC(AK) [1, d] is known to hold due to Schioppa [41, Theorem 1.6] (with simpler proofs appearing later due to Marchese and Merlo [32], Arroyo-Rabasa and Bouchitte [5] and Bate et al [8]).",
    "As we already stated in Subsection 1.1, FCC(AK) [d, d] was proven for every d ∈ N by DePhilippis and Rindler [20].",
